# Frontend vibecoding

## Intent

Ship **memorable**, production-grade UI — not generic “AI landing” templates. Pick a **clear aesthetic** (minimal luxe, brutal editorial, soft organic, etc.) and execute with **one strong type system**, **dominant color + sharp accent**, and **one hero motion idea** (staggered reveal, scroll choreography, tactile cards).

## Typography and color

- Prefer **character** over defaults: **two fonts only** — Playfair (display) + Inter (UI). Technical labels use Inter via `.text-technical` (tracked caps), not a third mono webfont. Extend via `--font-*` in `src/index.css` `@theme`.
- Use **CSS variables** (`--color-bg`, `--color-ink`, `--color-muted`, etc.) for cohesion; add new tokens in `@theme` when scaling the system.

## Motion (deps on hand)

- **`motion`**: component-level springs, layout, gestures.
- **`gsap`**: timelines, ScrollTrigger-style hero narratives (gate behind reduced-motion).
- **`@studio-freight/lenis`**: smooth scroll on marketing only; **disable or no-op** when `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`.

## Composition

- Functional components; extract hooks for scroll/animation/session state.
- Use `clsx` + `tailwind-merge` for conditional classes when utilities collide.
- **Spatial interest**: asymmetry, overlap, grid breaks, or generous whitespace — pick one lane and commit.

## Anti-patterns

- Purple-gradient-on-white clichés, cookie-cutter three-column feature grids with no brand tie-in.
- Animations that obscure **review verdicts**, **forms**, or **auth** — clarity beats flair on portal routes.

See `AGENTS.md` → **Specialist agents** for persona prompts (Vibe Architect, Motion Sorcerer, etc.).
